Greetings, jellyfish lovers! Jason Jaacks produced this new episode of Deep Look about Flower Hat jellies. Found off the coasts of Japan and Argentina, Flower Hat jellies (Olindias formosus) are small in size, just six inches across, and glow an iridescent green under blue light. We filmed at the Monterey Bay Aquarium.

You can read a story about jellyfish here: http://ww2.kqed.org/science/2015/09/29/why-jellyfish-float-like-a-butterfly-and-sting-like-a-bee/
